RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 5F All Weather Track CR: 66. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DR. FLASH DANCER broke in a bit at the start and crowded AFFIRM CHIEF, showed early speed and dictated terms to the turn, well handled while carving moderate fractions to the quarter marker, extended the lead into upper stretch and drew away under hand urging in the final sixteenth. AFFIRM CHIEF crowded by DR. FLASH DANCER at the start, was green in the early stages, chased the moderate early pace from the rail, finished evenly in the drive and was well clear in the end for third. MANY AMBITIONS took back in the early stages, advanced three wide on the turn, was outrun in upper stretch and did not mount a late rally. THECHIEFHASTRICKS lunged at the start and was off slowly, settled off of the moderate early pace, dropped back on the turn and tired in the drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 1M All Weather Track CR: 89. Claiming Purse 17000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MR NAVIGATOR rated off of the fast early pace, tracked the dueling pacesetters to the second turn, assumed command leaving the quarter marker, extended the lead in upper stretch and was set down for the drive, felt late pressure from HANS GRUBER, determinedly dug in in deep stretch and held that foe at bay in the final strides to prevail. HANS GRUBER allowed to settle, mounted a four wide rally into the stretch run, came within aim of MR NAVIGATOR inside of the furlong marker, battled the winner to deep stretch and was gamely bested in the final strides, while clear of the rest for second. SPEED GRAZY unhurried in the early stages, roused four then five wide into the stretch run, closed well in the late stages and was up for third in the final strides. NIGHT PROOF settled in the second flight, advanced on the second turn, angled three wide for the stretch drive, finished evenly in the final furlong and was outfinished for third. BORKAN sent to the early lead, set fast fractions while pressed by SUMO to the half-mile marker, was overtaken by MR NAVIGATOR leaving the quarter pole and faded in the stretch. SUMO hustled to be prominent in the early going, engaged with BORKAN and pressed that rival through fast fractions to the far turn, could not keep pace leaving the quarter marker and tired in the drive.

ENTRY.OWNER: Akin Zvika Avery Greg Gumina Jilda and Scoma Cheryl

ENTRY.NAME: Hans Gruber
ENTRY.OWNER: CNG Racing Stable Aiken Adam Bandemer Troy Bogdonoff Steve and Preiss Daniel

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 6F All Weather Track CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 14000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IRISH ROYALTY tracked the early pace, advanced while four wide or three deep nearing the turn, pressed the pace outside of ALTITUDE on the turn, assumed command leaving the quarter marker, switched leads nearing the sixteenth-marker and kept to task in deep stretch to prevail. BIG STICK crowded by ALTITUDE soon after the break, chased from the second flight, raced two wide to the quarter marker, tipped three wide for the drive, bumped ALTITUDE nearing the furlong grounds, made a good late rally inside of the furlong marker, could not reel in IRISH ROYALTY in the final stages and held safely for place. ALMONT broke in good order and was sent to the early lead, set decent fractions while racing in the two path to the quarter marker, lost the lead to IRISH ROYALTY nearing the top of the lane, chased that foe to mid-stretch, weakened in the final furlong and was clear for third in the late stages. LOKI OF ASGARD crowded soon after the break, showed good early speed and raced close to the pace heading to the turn, lost ground on the turn and lacked a late response. SUN AND SURF chased the early pace, was outrun on the turn, ran evenly in the stretch run and did not threaten in the late stages. ALTITUDE drifted in soon after the break and crowded LOKI OF ASGARD and BIG STICK, recovered and was forwardly placed in the early stages, pressed the pace between rivals to the quarter marker, was bumped by BIG STICK nearing the furlong marker and faded in the final furlong. UPDRAFT chased the early pace, lost contact on the turn and tired in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Loki of Asgard
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritts Catharina and Thomas Jamey R

ENTRY.OWNER: A Jason Hall Stables and Baker Stephen R
ENTRY.COMMENT: drifted in chute,close up,pressed pace,bumped foe 1/8,faded

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 1M All Weather Track CR: 60. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DRUIDIC crowded at the start by CORK MASTER, was unhurried in the early stages, trailed to the quarter marker, circled five wide for the drive, advanced nearing the furlong marker, mounted a bold late rally, overtook the top pair inside of the sixteenth-marker and edged away in the final strides. GROSS PROFIT forwardly placed in the early stages, prompted the modest pace to the second turn, battled with EYESA SPECIAL to mid-stretch, bumped with that rival nearing the sixteenth-marker, was overtaken by DRUIDIC in deep stretch and held safely in the end for place. EYESA SPECIAL sent from the inside leaving the break, set pedestrian fractions through the backstretch run, confronted by GROSS PROFIT nearing the top of the lane, battled with that foe to mid-stretch, could not keep pace inside of the furlong marker and weakened, while clear of the rest for show. START THEM UP allowed to settle, well positioned through the backstretch run, roused four wide nearing the quarter marker, could not sustain that effort in the drive and flattened in the late stages. LIBERTY WOLF a bit keen while in tight quarters on the first turn, tracked the modest pace while well placed through the backstretch run, slipped to the rail along the far turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch and did not produce a late rally. MIQUEAS forwardly placed in the early stages, stalked the modest fractions to the second turn, saved ground to the top of the lane, asked for run in mid-stretch and lacked a late response. CORK MASTER hopped leaving the start, impeded DRUIDIC and was away a step slowly, unhurried in the early stages, checked while in tight quarters nearing the far turn, lacked room approaching the top of the lane and tired in the final stages. PASSION OF JOE'S stalked the modest early pace, raced three wide to the half-mile marker, maintained position to the three-sixteenths marker and faded in the drive.

FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since October 15 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. (One win for $25,000 or less will not be considered when determining eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOB'S VAI off a half-step slowly then sent along the inside to establish the early lead, set moderate fractions through the turn, confronted by A ROUSING BABE in upper stretch, quickened when challenged by that rival nearing the furlong marker, determinedly held in deep stretch and kept to task in the final strides to prevail. A ROUSING BABE crowded by DANIELLE'S SECRET at the start and was off a step slowly, chased the moderate early pace, advanced two wide on the turn, confronted BOB'S VAI in upper stretch, lost a bit of ground to that rival nearing the furlong pole, re-rallied in deep stretch for one last attempt and could not get by the determined winner in the final strides, while besting the rest. PATSY MONTANA allowed to settle in the early stages, saved ground on the turn, advanced nearing the furlong marker, finished well in the final sixteenth and was up for third in the final strides. YODERANDO chased the moderate early pace, lost ground while four wide on the turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch, re-rallied inside of the furlong marker and just missed for show in the final strides. LOVE LOST unhurried in the early stages, swung widest for the stretch drive, ran evenly to mid-stretch and showed good late interest, while unable to impact the leaders. DANIELLE'S SECRET broke out and crowded A ROUSING BABE at the start, chased the moderate early pace, saved ground on the turn, advanced nearing the furlong marker and lacked a final kick in deep stretch. BET DE VRON broke alertly, ceded the early lead to BOB'S VAI and tracked that rival to the turn, raced three wide to the quarter marker and faded in the drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 6F All Weather Track CR: 95. Claiming Purse 23000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 15 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BETTOR TRIP NICK off a step slow then hustled to the front, set an uncontested lead to the quarter pole, repelled a challenge from WINDRIBBON at the top of the stretch, ran on well under aggressive handling and held off all late challengers. PAPAPIFAS broke well but did not engage for the early lead, saved all the ground into the turn, came under a ride from the five-sixteenths pole, gained on the leader despite racing on the wrong lead, swung out a path near the sixteenth pole and was gaining on the winner but ran out of ground. AWESOME DUDE came under a snug early hold and tracked the field from the rear of the compact field, was asked in earnest with a quarter mile to run, swung four wide into the stretch, was still last with a furlong to go but closed fast in deep stretch and gained the show. FOREIGN PROTOCOL tracked three wide under restraint down the backstretch, lost some ground near the half mile pole but rallied in the turn, continued to run on well through the stretch but was unable to improve position. WINDRIBBON tracked the early leader under restraint, moved to challenge on the turn, got to the flank of the leader approaching the eighth pole then tired in the final furlong.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 7 1M All Weather Track CR: 90. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $8,000. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUGAR BEETS settled in the second flight in the early going, raced between rivals while advancing nearing the half-mile marker, gained ground on the second turn, swung four then five wide for the drive, continued to rally in mid-stretch, closed determinedly in deep stretch, outfinished COOLCROSS in the late stages and prevailed in a drive in the final strides. COOLCROSS tracked the pace from the second flight in the early stages, saved ground while advancing on the second turn, made a three wide bid into the stretch run, chased THEYREMINISCEOVERU to mid-stretch, vied for the lead nearing the sixteenth-marker, met the bid of SUGAR BEETS in deep stretch and was gamely bested by that rival in the final strides, while holding safely in the end for second. THEYREMINISCEOVERU raced closest to the loose leader in the early stages, tracked DIAMOND BLITZ to the half-mile marker, vied for the lead while two wide nearing the quarter pole, assumed command in upper stretch and led to the furlong marker, could not keep pace in deep stretch and was outfinished for second, while holding for third. MAGIC TIGER threw his head at the start and was off a step slowly, was unhurried in the early stages, trailed into the second turn, advanced in upper stretch, lacked room in mid-stretch, found his best stride late and just missed for third. WELLSWORT (IRE) allowed to settle, made a steady gain on the backstretch and into the far turn, came in tight in upper stretch, ran evenly to mid-stretch and lacked a late response. POUR ON THE COLE took back off of the early pace and tracked from the second flight, advanced on the backstretch run, loomed three wide on the second turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch and flattened out in the final furlong. ON RAGLAN ROAD broke in the air and was away awkwardly, unhurried in the early stages, advanced while outside of rivals on the far turn, was outrun in upper stretch and did not threaten in the stretch. DIAMOND BLITZ away in good order and assumed command into the first turn, set decent fractions through the backstretch run, came under pressure nearing the quarter marker, overtaken leaving the far turn and tired in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Magic Tiger
ENTRY.COMMENT: threw head start,unhurried,bid 3/16,in tight 1/8,best stride late

ENTRY.NAME: On Raglan Road
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in air,unhurried,wide bid 2nd turn,flattened,no threat

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 6F All Weather Track CR: 90. Waiver Claiming Purse 17000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THUNDER OF ZION crowded at the start by DIAMOND RANGER and was off slowly, was unhurried in the early stages, raced two wide on the turn while improving position, angled four wide for the stretch run, closed willingly in the drive, responded to steady urging in deep stretch and offered a good late kick to prevail. DIAMOND RANGER bumped at the start by MIKE DAD then crowded THUNDER OF ZION and was off a step slowly, showed early speed and dictated terms to the turn, set pressured fractions to the quarter marker, battled for the lead to mid-stretch, could not hold off THUNDER OF ZION inside of the sixteenth-marker and held for second in the late stages. MY DOMINATOR chased the early quick pace from the second flight, advanced while saving ground on the turn, came in tight in upper stretch, was unable to find room while along the rail to the furlong grounds, found room inside of the furlong marker, was outkicked in deep stretch and held for show in the final strides. MAGICISTHEMOONLITE rated off of the solid early pace, was carried five to six wide nearing the quarter marker, regrouped in upper stretch, shifted out nearing the sixteenth-marker while rallying, finished well in the final stages and just missed for show. MIKE DAD broke out at the start and bumped DIAMOND RANGER, was hit in the head by an errant shoe in the early stages while chasing the pace, contested the pace to the outside of DIAMOND RANGER while two deep on the turn, lost ground in upper stretch and weakened in the drive. HEAT N REHEAT chased the solid early pace, saved ground to the top of the lane, ran evenly to mid-stretch and lacked a late response. ROYAL JESTER raced close to the early pace while outside of rivals, disputed the pace four then three wide on the turn, battled to mid-stretch and gave way in the final furlong. CINDERELLAS PRINCE showed early speed, chased the fast early pace between rivals, lost position into the turn, drifted out on the turn and carried out MAGICISTHEMOONLITE nearing the quarter marker, dropped back in upper stretch and tired in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Mike Dad
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out,hit with shoe early,pressed 2wide turn,weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Royal Jester
ENTRY.COMMENT: close up,contested pace 4-3wide turn,battled to 1/8,gave way late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 9 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 94. Allowance Purse 31000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since October 15 Allowed 3 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 5 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won The Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Add itional 2 lbs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIGNORINA MERISI (GB) broke alertly, was content to track the pace to the turn, awaited room, got clear running at the top of the stretch, quickened once clear and drew away under intermittent urging. ASCENDANCY angled towards to the three path after the break, tracked wide and from the rear of the field to the far turn, began a sustained run from the three furlong pole, swung six wide into the stretch, finished well and was second best in the end. VRONSKY FEINT broke well, was wide through both turns, swing five wide into the stretch and finished well to grab third. WORTHY OF MAGIC away best from the gate, set comfortable fractions alone on the lead, opened up some at the top of the stretch then weakened passing the eighth pole. NAUGHTY NADINE (GB) up close early, raced in tight quarters going into the clubhouse turn, settled into a tracking position three wide down the backstretch, made a strong bid to challenge for the lead in the stretch but stalled while racing on the wrong lead. TWILIGHT EMPIRE stumbled slightly then bumped with GRAZEN IN THE SUN at the break, lost momentum and spotted the field several lengths head start, made some forward progress while six wide down the backstretch, was hard ridden for more near the seven sixteenths pole, could not make up any ground but was ridden out and managed to pass a few stragglers in the end. ROSE DAWSON broke well but was not sent after the early pace, was content to lag behind the field to the far turn, was asked to pick it on on the turn but did not respond. ZELAIA was sent hard from the inside post to gain early position along the rail, stayed close while saving ground, was put into a drive past the three furlong pole, briefly loomed a threat then tired in the final furlong. GRAZEN IN THE SUN broke out and bumped with TWILIGHT EMPIRE at the break, was keen and hard to place going into the first turn, stalked the pacesetter to the far turn, was asked for more near the quarter pole but had nothing left and dropped back through the field.
